@page
@model AboutModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About";
}

<section class="fse-page-hero">
    <div class="fse-container-narrow">
        <span class="fse-badge">About</span>
        <h1>Who Built FSE and Why</h1>
        <p>A brief origin story &mdash; one creator, one company, one October.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="fse-section">
    <div class="fse-container-narrow fse-prose">
        <h2>Creator</h2>
        <p>
            FlowState Engineering was created by <strong>Scott Michael Wilson</strong> in October 2025.
            The first manifesto was drafted in a single sitting &mdash; ten tenets, one creed, and a
            conviction that AI-assisted development had become powerful enough to be dangerous without
            structure.
        </p>

        <h2>Origin</h2>
        <p>
            FSE is the engineering methodology used across eight production solutions in active development &mdash; across healthcare compliance, legal practice management, financial trading, elder care, education, corporate operations, chiropractic, and geotechnical engineering. The methodology is not a product &mdash; it is the operating system these projects run on. This site exists so the methodology can be read and understood without reverse-engineering it from the codebases that use it.
        </p>

        <h2>Origin</h2>
        <p>
            FSE was born from a specific recognition: AI-assisted development needed <strong>constraints, not
            freedom</strong>. Given unbounded latitude, the agent drifts, invents architecture mid-task, and
            ships subtle inconsistencies that compound across a solution. Given a short list of explicit
            standing orders, a clear session protocol, and a self-healing build loop, the same agent becomes
            the most consistent engineer on the team.
        </p>

        <p>
            The first manifesto captured the vision in October 2025. The words were philosophical because
            the practice didn't exist yet. Eight production solutions later, every tenet has a concrete
            engineering practice underneath it &mdash; the vision has become the machinery.
        </p>

        <div class="fse-callout">
            <p>
                <strong>The short version:</strong> FSE is what you get when you stop trying to make the agent
                more creative and start making the context more precise. The agent was never the bottleneck.
                The operating context was.
            </p>
        </div>

        <h2>Timeline</h2>
        <ol class="fse-timeline">
            <li class="fse-timeline-item">
                <span class="fse-timeline-step">October 2025</span>
                <h4>The Manifesto</h4>
                <p>Ten tenets, one creed. Written in the first hours of realization. Preserved on the <a asp-page="/Legacy">Legacy</a> page.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="fse-timeline-item">
                <span class="fse-timeline-step">Late 2025</span>
                <h4>First Solution</h4>
                <p>The first production system built under the methodology. Lessons from it became the first entries in the shared standing-order registry.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="fse-timeline-item">
                <span class="fse-timeline-step">2026</span>
                <h4>Eight Solutions Shipped</h4>
                <p>Healthcare, legal, financial, elder care, education, corporate operations. Different domains &mdash; same template, same bar, same document ecosystem.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="fse-timeline-item">
                <span class="fse-timeline-step">Today</span>
                <h4>FSE Is the Default</h4>
                <p>Every new solution onboards to the methodology in one CLI session. The template has absorbed the lessons of every prior build.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
            This site is a reference, not a lead form. If you're reading this for methodology research, the tenets and the How It Works page contain the whole system &mdash; there is nothing held back behind a wall.
        </p>

        <p class="fse-cta-center">
            <a class="fse-btn fse-btn-primary" asp-page="/HowItWorks">Read How FSE Works &rarr;</a>
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
